\title{Tradeoff analysis code}


\author{Karthik Ram}

\maketitle
Results from the tradeoff analysis thus far. The tradeoff between maturation rate and juvenile survival worked out fine for the most part.
\begin{knitrout}
\definecolor{shadecolor}{rgb}{0.969, 0.969, 0.969}\color{fgcolor}\begin{kframe}
\begin{alltt}
\hlfunctioncall{set.seed}(1121)
(x <- \hlfunctioncall{rnorm}(20))
\end{alltt}
\begin{verbatim}
##  [1]  0.14496  0.43832  0.15319  1.08494  1.99954 -0.81188  0.16027  0.58589  0.36009
## [10] -0.02531  0.15088  0.11008  1.35968 -0.32699 -0.71638  1.80977  0.50840 -0.52746
## [19]  0.13272 -0.15594
\end{verbatim}
\begin{alltt}
\hlfunctioncall{mean}(x)
\end{alltt}
\begin{verbatim}
## [1] 0.3217
\end{verbatim}
\begin{alltt}
\hlfunctioncall{var}(x)
\end{alltt}
\begin{verbatim}
## [1] 0.5715
\end{verbatim}
\end{kframe}
\end{knitrout}


The first element of \texttt{x} is 0.145. Boring boxplots
and histograms recorded by the PDF device:

\begin{knitrout}

    las = 1)
